<TITLE>Human resources development is UAE s top focus Culture Minister</TITLE>
<TEXT>
ABU DHABI 28th January 2017 WAM Investment in human resources and their development is at the heart of the UAE s national development strategy declared Sheikh Nahyan bin Mubarak Al Nahyan Minister of Culture and Knowledge Development The UAE also gives its citizens the opportunity to be informed of the best training programmes in major public and private companies and institutions so that they can get jobs and serve their nation Sheikh Nahyan stated ahead of the 11th edition of the recruitment show Tawdheef Abu Dhabi an event which is one of its kind in the UAE and attracts the best in the nation The event spread over an area of about 13 000 square metres will be held between January 30 and February 1 2017 at Abu Dhabi National Exhibition Centre It expects to attract more than 90 governmental and private agencies and institutions The show is a perfect opportunity for organisations seeking to enrich their workforces with competent and qualified Emirati cadres and meet with talented professionals in search of job opportunities It helps the public and private agencies find qualified cadres in the fields of health energy oil and gas industrial sector transportation logistics insurance banks financial institutions education tourism culture hospitality telecommunications and information technology safety security among others Companies attend the show to help familiarise graduates with the nature of work and the jobs available in their organisation market the Emiratisation programme for the target audience and build a strong database of all the talented Emirati applicants to meet the future recruitment needs Visitors to Tawdheef will have the opportunity to take part in an inspirational and high energy seminar programme to learn about the important skills needed for landing their dream job namely how to gain confidence to succeed at the workplace how to stand out as a candidate how to plan one s career progression and a number of self development tips on attracting recruiters and employers At the Tawdheef seminar programme visitors will learn how to plan their career by focussing on self development and transferable skills Share this article Featured Story Afghanistan s Defense Ministry says it wants to raise the number of women serving in the Afghan National Army to a level where women comprise 10 percent of the force Defense Ministry spokesman Mohammad Radmanesh said on January 27 that the government had set several measures including a special salary scale for female recruits to encourage more women to join up At this stage we have 1 575 Afghan women in our army ranks it is a mere 3 to 4 percent which is nothing Radmanesh said We are aiming to raise this percentage to 10 percent Radmanesh said there currently were about 400 Afghan women recruits training at Defense Ministry facilities Women serving in the military is a controversial topic in conservative Afghanistan Based on reporting by AFP and Tolonews com Latest Afghanistan Sun news By RFE RL The International Monetary Fund IMF says Afghanistan is experiencing a large influx of Afghanistan s Defense Ministry says it wants to raise the number of women serving in the 27 January 2017 Amid concerns of a severe humanitarian crisis induced by PanARMENIAN Net Afghanistan has announced fresh initiatives to bring more women into the army weeks PanARMENIAN Net Joking that opposites attract UK Prime Minister Theresa May called on President U S Donald 
